    ComputeSmallestCycles

    class ComputeSmallestCyclesDFS
extends AbstractComputeSmallestCycles
    This class offers the possibility to compute the smallest cycles and parikh vectors of a transitionsystem with a algorithm using the depth first search.

      • calculate

        private java.util.Set<Pair<java.util.List<java.lang.String>,ParikhVector>> calculate(TransitionSystem ts,
                                                                                     boolean smallest)
        Calculates the smallest cycles and their parikh vectors. It is important to notice, that in most cases if abcd is an cycle, that also bcda, cdab, etc. with the same parikh vector are cycle but won't be saved additionaly. Just in cases that two different passes coming the cycles, than they will be saved.
        Parameters:
        ts - - the transitionsystem to examine.
        smallest - - flag which tells if really all or just the smallest should be saved. (Storage vs. Time)
        Returns:
        a set of cycles and the belonging parikh vectors.
